The White House sent several nominations to the Senate on March 24, 2009. These nominations included Lael Brainard to be an Under Secretary of the Treasury, Johnnie Carson to be an Assistant Secretary of State (African Affairs), Cynthia J. Giles to be an Assistant Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, Kristina M. Johnson to be Under Secretary of Energy, Harold Hongju Koh to be Legal Adviser of the Department of State, and Joe Leonard, Jr. to be an Assistant Secretary of Agriculture. These nominations were to replace individuals who had resigned from their positions.